Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community,
Having regard to Council Directive 90/425/EEC of 26 June 1990 concerning the veterinary and zootechnical checks applicable in intra-Community trade in certain live animals and products with a view to the completion of the internal market (1), as last amended by Directive 92/118/EEC (2), and in particular Article 20 (3) thereof,
Whereas, to ensure the operation of the Animo computer network the various units referred to in Article 1 of Decision/398/EEC (3) should be identified and an updated list made;
Whereas the list must be updated and consolidated to introduce new usage charges for the Member States from 1 April 1996;
Whereas the numerous amendments made to the Animo units over the last three years following the accession of Austria, Finland and Sweden, changes in the regional organization of the Member States and Commission approval of the border inspection posts has made it necessary to adopt a new Decision; where Commission Decision 92/175/EEC (4) should therefore be repealed; whereas repeal of that Decision does not affect the Acts and Decisions referring to it;
Whereas the measures provided for in this Decision are in accordance with the opinion of the Standing Veterinary Committee,
